      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/notification/CpsDataUpdatedEventFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 73,
      "message": "@SneakyThrows fakes out the compiler. In other words, Lombok doesn't wrap or replace the thrown checked exception, but makes the compiler think that it is an unchecked exception.\n\nIn other words, this is a way to bypass exceptions at compile time. But in my opinion this should not be the correct way of handling exceptions, because the bypassed exception can show weird behaviour at runtime.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
